The paper proposes a novel fully convolutional neural network for facial landmark localization, which is a common task in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed network also involves progressive representation learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions a large-scale benchmark for facial landmark localization, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
